 First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes was born in 1219, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William Foliot in 1245, in Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1219–":"1219–Surnud","1215–1268":"1215–1268","1247–1315":"1247–1315","1219–Female":"1219–Surnud","1315":"1315","1215":"1215","1247":"1247","1268":"1268","1245":"1245","1219":"1219","17 January 1247":"17. jaanuar 1247","Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1219–":"1219–Kuollut","1215–1268":"1215–1268","1247–1315":"1247–1315","1219–Female":"1219–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1215":"1215","1247":"1247","1268":"1268","1245":"1245","1219":"1219","17 January 1247":"17. tammikuuta 1247","Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1219–":"1219–Décédée","1215–1268":"1215–1268","1247–1315":"1247–1315",